annotationA: Transcription factor B5 is a subunit of the basal transcription and DNA repair factor TFIIH, which operates in transcription and DNA repair
annotationB: Cyclin-T; Regulatory subunit of the cyclin-dependent kinase pair (CDK9/cyclin T) complex, also called positive transcription elongation factor B (P-TEFb), which is proposed to facilitate the transition from abortive to production elongation by phosphorylating the CTD (carboxy-terminal domain) of the large subunit of RNA polymerase II (RNAP II)
